    {"doc_id": "cloud_003", "title": "Service mesh and Istio traffic management",
     "body": "A service mesh handles inter-service communication with features like mTLS, circuit breaking, retries, and observability. Istio injects a sidecar Envoy proxy into each pod to intercept all network traffic. Traffic policies, virtual services, and destination rules control routing, load balancing, and fault injection.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "networking"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_004", "title": "Distributed tracing with OpenTelemetry",
     "body": "OpenTelemetry provides vendor-neutral APIs for traces, metrics, and logs. A trace spans a request across multiple services; each span records timing, service name, and attributes. Sampling is essential to manage volume: head-based sampling decides at trace start, tail-based sampling waits for full trace context.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "observability"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_005", "title": "PostgreSQL query optimisation and indexes",
     "body": "PostgreSQL uses a cost-based query planner that estimates I/O and CPU costs for alternative execution plans. B-tree indexes support equality and range queries; GIN indexes support full-text and JSONB searches; BRIN indexes are compact for monotonically increasing columns. EXPLAIN ANALYZE reveals actual row counts and execution times.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "databases"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_006", "title": "Redis caching patterns and eviction",
     "body": "Redis supports multiple eviction policies: LRU, LFU, TTL-based, and random. Cache-aside loads data into cache on miss; write-through writes to cache and database simultaneously. Thundering herd occurs when cache expires and many requests hit the database simultaneously. Probabilistic early expiration or distributed locks mitigate this.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "databases"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_007", "title": "AWS S3 storage classes and cost optimisation",
     "body": "S3 offers multiple storage classes: Standard (frequent access), Intelligent-Tiering (auto-moves), Glacier Instant Retrieval, Glacier Flexible Retrieval, and Glacier Deep Archive. S3 Lifecycle policies automatically transition objects between classes. S3 outbound data transfer costs are often the dominant cost driver in cloud architectures.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "aws"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_008", "title": "Container image security and supply chain",
     "body": "Container image vulnerabilities include base image CVEs, vulnerable dependencies, and secrets in layers. SBOM (Software Bill of Materials) documents all components. Sigstore/Cosign enables cryptographic signing of images. Distroless base images reduce attack surface by including only the runtime, not package managers or shells.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "security"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_009", "title": "Kafka stream processing and consumer groups",
     "body": "Apache Kafka stores messages in ordered, immutable partitioned logs with configurable retention. Consumer groups allow horizontal scaling: each partition is consumed by exactly one group member. Exactly-once semantics requires idempotent producers and transactional consumers. Kafka Streams and ksqlDB enable stateful stream processing.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "streaming"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_010", "title": "Zero-trust network architecture",
     "body": "Zero-trust assumes no implicit trust based on network location. Every request is authenticated, authorised, and encrypted. Micro-segmentation limits lateral movement between services. SPIFFE/SPIRE provides workload identity; BeyondCorp applies zero-trust to enterprise networks. SDP (Software-Defined Perimeter) replaces VPN-based perimeter security.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "security"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_011", "title": "Terraform infrastructure as code",
     "body": "Terraform provisions cloud infrastructure declaratively: you describe desired state and Terraform plans the diff. The state file records current resource state; remote state in S3 or Terraform Cloud enables team collaboration. Workspaces isolate environments. Modules encapsulate reusable patterns. Drift occurs when manual changes bypass Terraform.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "devops"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_012", "title": "Chaos engineering and failure injection",
     "body": "Chaos engineering deliberately injects failures to test system resilience. Netflix Chaos Monkey randomly terminates EC2 instances. Simian Army extended this to AZ outages, network latency injection, and security group misconfigurations. GameDays simulate major incidents in production to discover gaps in runbooks and alerting.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "reliability"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_013", "title": "Content delivery networks and edge caching",
     "body": "CDNs cache content at edge nodes close to users, reducing origin load and improving latency. Cache-Control headers control TTL. Purging stale content is challenging at scale: CDNs offer tag-based or URL-pattern purge APIs. Edge computing (Cloudflare Workers, Lambda@Edge) runs code at CDN nodes to personalise responses.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "networking"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_014", "title": "Database sharding and horizontal partitioning",
     "body": "Sharding splits a database across multiple nodes by partitioning the keyspace. Range sharding assigns contiguous key ranges to shards but can create hot spots. Hash sharding distributes evenly but makes range queries expensive. Consistent hashing minimises resharding cost when nodes are added. Cross-shard queries require scatter-gather.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "databases"},
    {"doc_id": "cloud_015", "title": "Observability: metrics, logs, and traces",
     "body": "The three pillars of observability are metrics (aggregated numeric data over time), logs (structured event records), and traces (request flows across services). Metrics enable dashboards and alerting; logs provide debugging detail; traces reveal latency bottlenecks. The OpenTelemetry Collector unifies instrumentation across all three signals.",
     "domain": "cloud", "source": "observability"},

